<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1335,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,1495,1521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Description.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[521,670,1496,1522]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="3.8" valueMax="4.1" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4.1 mm</quantity>
; habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[852,926,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[910,926,1496,1522]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
. Coloration: head dark brown to blackish brown; pronotum brown to blackish brown, of similar coloration as head or paler; elytra brown to dark brown, slightly paler than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[497,585,1576,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Habitus and forebody of Amarochara species. 19 — habitus of A. freyi (Bernhauer) (holotype); 20 — forebody of A. formicina sp. n.; 21 — forebody of A. inquilina (Casey). Scale bars: 20 – 21: 1.0 mm; 19 without scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175619/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[552,585,1576,1602]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); abdomen reddish brown, with posterior margins of tergites III–VI, posterior 
<number box="[226,236,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[247,263,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="2.0">2</number>
– 
<number box="[281,291,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[302,316,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
of tergite VII, and segments VIII–X reddish yellow; legs yellowish brown; antennae dark brown, with antennomeres I–II/III and XI slightly paler.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1335,2002]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,738]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Head posteriorly without distinct neck, approximately as wide as long and of subquadrate shape, lateral margins subparallel in dorsal view; microsculpture conspicuously coarse, surface almost completely matt, only frons with small areas with slightly less pronounced microsculpture and subdued shine (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1373,1776,1802]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1389,1422,1776,1802]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Habitus and forebody of Amarochara species. 19 — habitus of A. freyi (Bernhauer) (holotype); 20 — forebody of A. formicina sp. n.; 21 — forebody of A. inquilina (Casey). Scale bars: 20 – 21: 1.0 mm; 19 without scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175619/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">20</figureCitation>
); puncturation fine, indistinguishable from microsculpture; eyes moderately large, slightly shorter than postocular region in dorsal view; genal carina very fine (
<figureCitation box="[734,805,1856,1882]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[788,805,1856,1882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpus slender, preapical palpomere more than 
<number box="[210,225,1896,1922]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
times as long as wide. Antennae stout and relatively short; antennomere I approximately 
<number box="[1294,1331,1896,1922]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as wide and with pronounced dorso-apical furrow; II approximately as long as I; III somewhat shorter than II, coniform, and approximately 
<number box="[606,643,1976,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as wide; IV almost twice as wide as long; V–X of increasing width and increasingly transverse, X at least 
<number box="[799,814,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
times as wide as long; XI of ovoid shape and slightly longer than the combined length of IX–X (
<figureCitation box="[652,724,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[706,724,192,218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Pronotum approximately 
<number box="[501,552,232,258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" value="1.15">1.15</number>
times as wide as long and 
<number box="[877,914,232,258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" value="1.3">1.3</number>
times as wide as head, maximal width near the moderately marked posterior angles; microsculpture as coarse as or even more pronounced than that of head, but surface slightly more shiny; puncturation not discernible in microsculpture; pubescence pale and depressed, denser and more distinct than that of head (
<figureCitation box="[787,870,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[883,916,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Habitus and forebody of Amarochara species. 19 — habitus of A. freyi (Bernhauer) (holotype); 20 — forebody of A. formicina sp. n.; 21 — forebody of A. inquilina (Casey). Scale bars: 20 – 21: 1.0 mm; 19 without scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175619/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Elytra approximately 
<number box="[458,509,392,418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" value="1.25">1.25</number>
times as wide and at suture 
<number box="[858,895,392,418]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" value="0.8">0.8</number>
times as long as pronotum; posterior margin very shallowly sinuate near posterior angles; puncturation dense, moderately fine, and ill-defined; microsculpture shallow, much less pronounced than that of head and pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1013,1101,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1118,1151,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[313,1273,1298,1862]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Habitus and forebody of Amarochara species. 19 — habitus of A. freyi (Bernhauer) (holotype); 20 — forebody of A. formicina sp. n.; 21 — forebody of A. inquilina (Casey). Scale bars: 20 – 21: 1.0 mm; 19 without scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175619/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">20</figureCitation>
); mesosternum without median carina; mesosternal process long and apically acute, reaching more than halfway between mesocoxae. Metatarsomere I longer than the combined length of II–III, but shorter than the combined length of II–IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Abdominal tergites III–V with moderately deep, densely punctured, but not carinate anterior impressions, remainder of these tergites with less dense and more well-defined puncturation; puncturation of posterior tergites much sparser than that of anterior tergites; microsculpture present, but shallow (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1222,672,698]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1206,1222,672,698]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergite X anteriorly not distinctly elongated and rather broad.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" targetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1953,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,323,1953,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">FIGURES 1–7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[330,574,1954,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Amarochara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[330,574,1954,1977]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Amarochara formicina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[582,642,1953,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[582,642,1953,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
1—habitus; 2—forebody; 3—head in lateral view; 4—antenna; 5—abdomen; 6—male tergite VIII; 7—male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2–7: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
ɗ: tergite VIII posteriorly truncate (
<figureCitation box="[618,690,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[673,690,152,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of sternite VIII truncate and with dense long marginal setae (
<figureCitation box="[337,410,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[284,1283,797,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[283,1304,797,1927]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Amarochara formicina sp. n. 1 — habitus; 2 — forebody; 3 — head in lateral view; 4 — antenna; 5 — abdomen; 6 — male tergite VIII; 7 — male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2 – 7: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175616/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[393,410,192,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
); median lobe of aedeagus with ventral process approximately as long as basal capsule and laterally carinate; ventral process apically shallowly incised; internal sac with rather long flagellum (
